'''10''' (''[[2008â2009 figure skating season|2008â2009]]'') |combined total= 172.47 |combined date= [[2010 World Figure Skating Championships|2010 World Championships]] |SP score= 60.52 |SP date= [[2010 World Figure Skating Championships|2010 World Championships]] |FS score= 111.95 |FS date= [[2010 World Figure Skating Championships|2010 World Championships]] }} '''Caydee Denney''' (born June 22, 1993) is an [[United States|American]] [[Pair skating|pair skater]]. She currently skates with [[John Coughlin (figure skater)|John Coughlin]]. With former partner [[Jeremy Barrett (figure skater)|Jeremy Barrett]], she won the 2010 [[2010 United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national championship]]. She also competed as a [[single skating|single skater]] until 2009. == Career == === Partnership with Barrett === Denney and Barrett first began skating together in 2006, but the partnership did not last. They teamed up again in 2008 and began competing in the 2008-2009 season. Based on their good performance during the summer non-qualifying competitions, Denney and Barrett were assigned to the [[2008 Nebelhorn Trophy]], where they placed 4th. They won the 2009 [[Eastern Sectional Figure Skating Championships]] to qualify for the national championships. Denney and Barrett won the silver medal at the [[2009 United States Figure Skating Championships|2009 U.S. Nationals]]. They placed sixth at the [[2009 Four Continents Figure Skating Championships|2009 Four Continents]]. The following season they won the [[2010 United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national title]] and the right to compete at the Olympics, where they finished 13th. They placed 7th at the [[2010 World Figure Skating Championships|2010 World Championships]]. At the [[2011 United States Figure Skating Championships|2011 U.S. Nationals]], they won the bronze medal and were assigned to compete at Four Continents, however they were forced to withdraw; Denney accidentally sliced Barrett's calf on his right leg while practicing side-by-side jumps. Denney and Barrett ended their partnership in February 2011. === Partnership with Coughlin === On May 17, 2011, Denney announced that she had teamed up with [[John Coughlin (figure skater)|John Coughlin]]. They train under coach [[Dalilah Sappenfield]] at the Broadmoor Skating Club in [[Colorado Springs, Colorado]], Denney having relocated from [[Wesley Chapel, Florida]] after splitting from her previous partner. Denney and Coughlin have a height difference of 14 inches (36 cm). They made their competitive debut at the Liberty Summer competition in July 2011, winning the short program. == Personal life == Caydee Denney was born in [[Ocala, Florida]].
